3️⃣ Production — Context Tuning
🔹 Core Concepts
Context tuning ensures the LLM uses only relevant information without exceeding token limits.
Techniques:
Chunking + scoring → rank documents by relevance
Sliding window context → feed recent/high-priority context first
Truncation strategies → keep essential context, discard less relevant
Embedding similarity threshold → discard low-similarity docs
🔹 Python Example — Context Filtering
threshold = 0.7
relevant_docs = [doc for idx, doc in enumerate(documents) if cos_sim[idx] >= threshold]
context = " ".join(relevant_docs)
print("Filtered Context for LLM:", context)

GS-Level Insight:

Proper context tuning → reduces hallucinations, improves answer relevance
Production monitoring → track retriever precision, token usage, latency
4️⃣ Scenario-Based Questions — GS-Level
Scenario	How to Answer
“LLM response ignores key context”	Use context filtering, chunking, and relevance scoring; log which docs were used.
“Too many tokens, query fails”	Implement sliding window or truncation, prioritize recent/high-score documents.
“Low-quality retrieval affects answers”	Improve retriever embeddings, tune thresholds, or expand document coverage.
“RAG system is slow in production”	Cache frequent queries, batch embeddings, monitor vector DB latency.
“Fraud alert missed due to context”	Tune similarity thresholds, include risk-critical transactions, log retrieval hits/misses.
